ter part of the 20th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Neal","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Neil ."]},{"name":"Neale","meanings":["Latin: Dark, swarthy; blacksmith."]},{"name":"Neil","meanings":["Anglicized form of the enduringly popular Gaelic name   Niall .  From the Middle Ages onwards, this name was found mainly in Ireland, the Highlands of Scotland, and the English-Scottish Border region. However, since the 20th century it has spread to enjoy considerable popularity in all parts of the English-speaking world, although in England it has recently been overtaken by the Gaelic form."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Niell was born about 1150, in Argyll, Scotland, his father, Cu Duilig Abbot Of Lismore, was 27 and his mother, Unknown, was 35. He married Unknown before 1156, in Hebrides, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1150–":"umbes 1150–Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1140–Female":"1140–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1125–Male":"1125–Surnud","1117–Female":"1117–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1117":"1117","about 1170":"umbes 1170","before 1136":"enne 1136","before 1156":"enne 1156","1125":"1125","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","Hebrides, Scotland":"Hebrides, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1150–":"noin 1150–Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1140–Female":"1140–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1125–Male":"1125–Kuollut","1117–Female":"1117–Kuollut","about 1150":"noin 1150","1117":"1117","about 1170":"noin 1170","before 1136":"ennen vuotta 1136","before 1156":"ennen vuotta 1156","1125":"1125","1110":"1110","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","Hebrides, Scotland":"Hebrides, Scotland","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"about 1150–":"environ 1150–Décédé","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1140–Female":"1140–Décédée","1170–Male":"1170–Décédé","1125–Male":"1125–Décédé","1117–Female":"1117–Décédée","about 1150":"environ 1150","1117":"1117","about 1170":"environ 1170","b